<TITLE> South Africa's Mbeki agrees to step down </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 JOHANNESBURG, Sep 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - South African President Thabo Mbeki has agreed to resign after his ruling ANC announced that it would remove him from office before the end of his term, Mbeki's office said on Saturday. "Following the decision of the National Executive Committee of the African National Congress to recall President Thabo Mbeki, the President has obliged and will step down after all constitutional requirements have been met," the presidency said.
